      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZORBA DAN (1) was in the money two starts ago then things went amiss last start when he broke and finished 30 metres away in sixth over 1780m at this track. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Big chance if he behaves in this similar assignment. JOVIAL JODI (5) resumes from a spell of five months after closing off last campaign in good form, the last run being a solid third over 1780m at this track. Sure to be right there at the finish. MACKENZIE REG (7) is a two-year-old filly by A Rocknroll Dance from Dougies Envy on debut. Can settle just behind them and wait on the sprint lane. Has the right credentials to play a major role. WAVE OF DELIGHT (8) is stepping out for the first time. By Downbytheseaside and hails from the Wayne Graham stable. Well-placed to score at his first appearance.",
